<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4747218>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 32. Tornipora canui (Brydone); Cretaceous, late Campanian (Belemnitella mucronata Zone), Trimingham, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom; NHMUK D8000, Brydone Collection; (a) autozooids and an avicularium; cowl-like structure marked by an arrow may be an intramural avicularium budded within an autozooid; (b) autozooids showing lateral constrictions in the opesiae and oral spine bases; (c) autozooid (left) and avicularium (right). Scale bars: a = 500 µm; b, c = 100 µm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4747218/files/figure.png" .

